      "complexity": "Paxos is more abstract and harder to understand; Raft is designed for practical implementation with clearer semantics.",
      "quorum_usage": "Both require strict majorities, but Paxos applies it per-proposal while Raft applies it per-term and per-log-entry replication.",
      "liveness": "Paxos requires a distinguished proposer for guaranteed liveness; Raft guarantees liveness through leader election and term advancement."
    }
  }
